OL,6,FA police officer attended Heslop's
OL,7,Fhome and told her there was no basis
OL,8,Fto arrest Mr Hardy.
OL,10,FLater that day, Heslop waited near Mr
OL,11,FHardy's house to carry out the attack
OL,12,Fon him as he returned from some shops
OL,13,Fnearby, before walking back to her own
OL,14,Fhome.
OL,16,FProsecutor Sharon Beattie KC said
OL,17,FHeslop lived on the same road and
OL,18,Fadded: "She was significantly
OL,19,Fphysically stronger than the deceased
OL,20,Fand there was weight lifting and other
OL,21,Fgym equipment in her home."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/8
