OL,6,FWhen Northumbria Police officers
OL,7,Farrived and informed Heslop she was
OL,8,Fbeing arrested for Mr Hardy's murder,
OL,9,Fshe said: "Oh he's never died, has he?"
OL,11,FHeslop was charged with murder and
OL,12,Finitially pleaded not guilty to the
OL,13,Foffence. She was due to stand trial at
OL,14,FNewcastle Crown Court in March but
OL,15,Fdays before the hearing was due to
OL,16,Fbegin she pleaded guilty.
OL,18,FOn Friday 24 October, Heslop, was
OL,19,Fsentenced to life in prison, serving a
OL,20,Fminimum of 20 years.
